Pineapple Upside Down Cake
  --Haliâ€™imaile General Store

1 large fresh pineapple
2/3 c butter 
1 c firmly packed light brown sugar 
3/4 c sugar 
3 tbsp butter 
4 egg yolks 
1/3 c cake flour 
1 tbsp baking powder 
1/2 c whole milk 
1 tbsp vanilla extract 
salt

Prepare 4x8oz ramekins. Trim top and bottom of pineapple and remove skin. Slice into 4 thick rings, removing the core. Trim pineapple rings to fit ramekins. Set aside. To make the caramel, melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Add brown sugar and stir until smooth. Remove from heat and set aside. Using a hand mixer, cream butter and sugar for 3 min. Add egg yolks and mix at medium speed for 1 min. Sift cake flour, baking powder and salt together. Add flour mixture to butter-sugar-egg mixture and mix on low. Slowly add milk and vanilla. Mix for another 30 s. Spread caramel evenly over bottom of ramekins. Place pineapple rings on top of caramel base. Pour cake batter over the pineapple ring, leaving a 1/4" space at ramekin top. Transfer ramekins on a baking sheetand bake at 300F for 35 min. Rotate ramekins and bake another 10 minutes until center is cooked. Remove from oven and cool 5 min. Carefully invert ramekins to release cake on serving plate. 
